==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|xno}} ''[[siute]]'', from {{etyl|fro}} ''[[sieute]]'' (modern [[suite]]), originally a participle adjective from vulgar Latin ''*sequita'' (for Classical Latin ''[[secuta]]''), from Latin {{term|sequi||to follow}}, because the component garments "follow each other", i.e. are worn together.

